<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 12:48PM MST  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>Expect breezy to moderate winds this afternoon into early evening
with sustained winds over 20 to 30 mph with gusts around 40 mph
with localized areas gusting to around 50 mph. This will create
blowing and drifting snow making roadways hazardous. New snow is
possible but will be light for the Teton Valley, around 1 to 4
inches. For the Blackfoot mountains lower elevations will be
relatively warm and not get a lot of new snow. Higher elevations,
above 6000 feet, expect 2 to 5 inches of new snow this afternoon
into early evening.
Another round of wind and, to a lesser degree, snow is expected
mainly Friday afternoon into Friday evening as well.</description>
